#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:0.5"
msgid "57. Nahānasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.57\">Monks’ Confession 57: the training rule on "
"bathing</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.117
#. VAR: samayena → atha kho (bj, s1-3)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2>\n"
"<h3 id=\"anunidana1\">First sub-story</h3>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.57.1\">Bu-Pc.57.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\""
" id=\"BD.2.401\">BD.2.401</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1088</a>At one time the "
"Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū tapode nahāyanti."
msgstr "At that time the monks were bathing in the hot springs."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro “sīsaṃ nahāyissāmī”ti "
"tapodaṃ gantvā—"
msgstr ""
"On one occasion King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha wanted to wash his head, <a "
"class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.117\">Vin.4.117</a> and he went to the hot "
"springs. "

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.4"
msgid "“yāvāyyā nahāyantī”ti ekamantaṃ paṭimānesi."
msgstr "He waited respectfully for the monks to finish,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.5"
msgid "Bhikkhū yāva samandhakārā nahāyiṃsu."
msgstr "but they kept on bathing until dark."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro vikāle sīsaṃ nahāyitvā, nagaradvāre "
"thakite bahinagare vasitvā, kālasseva asambhinnena vilepanena yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Only then was King Bimbisāra able to wash his head. But because the town "
"gates had been shut, he had to spend the night outside the city.</p>\n"
"<p>In the morning, with his make-up still on,<span class=\"note\" hidden><i "
"lang=\"pi\">Asambhinnena vilepanena</i>, an unusual expression. According to "
"<span class=\"ref\">Sp-ṭ.3.357</span><i lang=\"pi\">asambhinnena</i> means “"
"with [make-up] not smeared, not lost,” <i lang=\"pi\">amakkhitena, "
"anaṭṭhena</i>.</span> he went to the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.7"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, and sat down."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.8"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ seniyaṃ bimbisāraṃ bhagavā etadavoca—"
msgstr "The Master said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.9"
msgid "“kissa tvaṃ, mahārāja, kālasseva āgato asambhinnena vilepanenā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Great King, why have you come early in the morning with your make-up still "
"on?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.10"
msgid "Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "The King told him what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ seniyaṃ bimbisāraṃ dhammiyā kathāya "
"sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr ""
"The Master then instructed, inspired, and gladdened him with a teaching,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.12"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito "
"samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā "
"padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"after which the King rose from his seat, bowed down, circumambulated the "
"Master with his right side towards him, and departed."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ "
"sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1089</a>The Master had the Order of monks assembled "
"and asked them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.14"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū rājānampi passitvā na mattaṃ jānitvā "
"nahāyantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Is it true, monks, that monks bathed without moderation, even after seeing "
"the King?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.15"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr ""
"<a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.402\">BD.2.402</a> “It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.16"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.17"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā rājānampi passitvā na mattaṃ "
"jānitvā nahāyissanti."
msgstr ""
"How can those foolish men bathe without moderation, even after seeing the "
"King?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.19"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.20"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h3 id=\"anupannatti1\">First preliminary ruling</h3>\n"
"<p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1090</a>‘If a monk bathes at intervals "
"of less than a half-month, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:1.21"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"<p class=\"endsection\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1091</a>In this way the Master "
"laid down this training rule for the monks.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:2.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū uṇhasamaye pariḷāhasamaye kukkuccāyantā na "
"nahāyanti, sedagatena gattena sayanti."
msgstr ""
"<h3 id=\"anunidana2\">Second sub-story</h3>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.57.2\">Bu-Pc.57.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1092</a>Soon afterwards, because they were afraid of wrongdoing, the monks "
"did not bathe when it was hot or when they had a fever, and they went to "
"sleep covered in sweat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:2.1.2"
msgid "Cīvarampi senāsanampi dussati."
msgstr "As a consequence their robes and the furniture were soiled."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:2.1.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:2.1.4"
msgid ""
"anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uṇhasamaye pariḷāhasamaye orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“<strong class=\"rule\">Monks, if it’s hot or you have a fever, I allow you "
"to bathe at intervals of less than a half-month.</strong>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:2.1.5"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

