"sarajena vātena okiṇṇā honti."
msgstr ""
"<h3 id=\"anunidana6\">Sixth sub-story</h3>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.57.6\">Bu-Pc.57.6</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1104</a>Soon afterwards a number of monks were making robes out in the "
"open, and they were assailed by dusty winds"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:6.1.2"
msgid "Devo ca thokaṃ thokaṃ phusāyati."
msgstr "and fine rain."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:6.1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā na nahāyanti, kilinnena gattena sayanti."
msgstr ""
"But because they were afraid of wrongdoing, they did not bathe afterwards, "
"and they went to sleep while still moist."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:6.1.4"
msgid "Cīvarampi senāsanampi dussati."
msgstr ""
"As a consequence their robes and the furniture <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\""
"Vin.4.119\">Vin.4.119</a> were soiled."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:6.1.5"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:6.1.6"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vātavuṭṭhisamaye orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“<strong class=\"rule\">Monks, if there is wind and rain, I allow you to "
"bathe at intervals of less than a half-month.</strong>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:6.1.7"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc18
#. VAR: nahāyeyya → nhāyeyya (s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: orenaddhamāsaṃ → orenaḍḍhamāsaṃ (s1-3)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:6.1.8"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2>\n"
"<p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1105</a>‘If a monk bathes at intervals "
"of less than a half-month, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:6.1.9"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "These are the appropriate reasons:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:6.1.10"
msgid ""
"Diyaḍḍho māso seso gimhānanti vassānassa paṭhamo māso iccete aḍḍhateyyamāsā "
"uṇhasamayo, pariḷāhasamayo, gilānasamayo, kammasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo, "
"vātavuṭṭhisamayo—"
msgstr ""
"it is the two-and-a-half-month period of the hot season and the fever "
"season, comprising the last one-and-a-half months of summer and the first "
"month of the rains; he is sick; he is working; he is traveling; there is "
"wind and rain.’”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:6.1.11"
msgid "ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc19
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.57.7\"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-"
"Pc.57.7.1\">Bu-Pc.57.7.1</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1106</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"<gloss>… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.6"
msgid "Orenaddhamāsanti"
msgstr ""
"p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1107</a><term>At intervals of less than a half-"
"month</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.7"
msgid "ūnakaddhamāsaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>after less than a half-month.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.8"
msgid "Nahāyeyyāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1108</a><term>Bathes</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.9"
msgid "cuṇṇena vā mattikāya vā nahāyati, payoge payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if he bathes with bath powder or soap, then for every action, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct.<span class=\"note\" hidden><i lang=\""
"pli\">Mattika</i>. I translate both <i lang=\"pli\">cuṇṇa</i> and <i lang=\""
"pli\">mattika</i> according to function rather than substance. <i lang=\""
"pli\">Cuṇṇa</i> is powder used for a number of purposes, including medical "
"ones, and <i lang=\"pli\">mattika</i> is clay, but in this context both are "
"used as cleaning agents. There are a number of Canonical passages that show "
"them as the two principal agents for cleaning the body. At <span class=\""
"ref\">MS.3.261</span> and a number of similar passages, we find that the two "
"would always be made ready before entering the <i lang=\"pli\">jantāghara</i>"
", the sauna/bathroom. In the present rule, this very definition states that "
"bathing includes the use of powder and/or clay. At <span class=\"ref\""
">MS.4.2127-MS.3.2128</span> the nuns are prohibited from bathing with powder "
"or scented clay, but should use ordinary clay instead. In the commentaries, "
"at <span class=\"ref\">Sp.3.33</span>, we find that clay is used for washing "
"one’s hair: <i lang=\"pli\">Kesā panassa sayameva mattikaṃ gahetvā "
"dhovitabbā.</i></span>"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.10"
msgid "Nahānapariyosāne, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"At the end of the bath, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.11"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1109</a><term>Unless there is an appropriate "
"reason</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.12"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>except at an appropriate time.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.13"
msgid "Uṇhasamayo nāma"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.405\">BD.2.405</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1110</a><term>The hot season</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.14"
msgid "diyaḍḍho māso seso gimhānaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>the last month-and-a-half of summer.</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.15"
msgid "Pariḷāhasamayo nāma"
msgstr "<term>The fever season</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.16"
msgid ""
"vassānassa paṭhamo māso “iccete aḍḍhateyyamāsā uṇhasamayo pariḷāhasamayo”ti "
"nahāyitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>the first month of the rainy season. During the two-and-a-half-month "
"period of the hot season and the fever season, he may bathe.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.17"
msgid "Gilānasamayo nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1111</a><term>He is sick</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.18"
msgid "yassa vinā nahānena na phāsu hoti."
msgstr "<gloss>he is not comfortable without bathing."

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.19"
msgid "Gilānasamayoti nahāyitabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he is sick, he may bathe.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.20"
msgid "Kammasamayo nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1112</a><term>He is working</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.21"
msgid "antamaso pariveṇampi sammaṭṭhaṃ hoti."
msgstr "<gloss>even if he just sweeps the precincts of a building."

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.22"
msgid "“Kammasamayo”ti nahāyitabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he is doing work, he may bathe.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.23"
msgid "Addhānagamanasamayo nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1113</a><term>He is traveling</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.24"
msgid ""
"“addhayojanaṃ gacchissāmī”ti nahāyitabbaṃ, gacchantena nahāyitabbaṃ, gatena "
"nahāyitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if he intends to travel six kilometers,<span class=\"note\" hidden>"
"Half a <i lang=\"pi\">yojana</i>. The length of a <i lang=\"pi\">yojana</i> "
"is uncertain, and perhaps it never was a precise distance. But a reasonable "
"estimate is 8 miles or just under 13 kilometers (see ACMC, p.16). Thus half "
"a <i lang=\"pi\">yojana</i> is just over 6 km.</span> he may bathe; while "
"traveling, he may bathe; after he has traveled, he may bathe.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc27
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.25"
msgid "Vātavuṭṭhisamayo nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1114</a><term>There is wind and rain</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.26"
msgid ""
"bhikkhū sarajena vātena okiṇṇā honti, dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni kāye "
"patitāni honti."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>monks are assailed by dusty winds, and two or three drops of rain "
"have fallen on their bodies."

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.1.27"
msgid "“Vātavuṭṭhisamayo”ti nahāyitabbaṃ."
msgstr "If there is wind and rain, they may bathe.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc28
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.2.1"
msgid ""
"Ūnakaddhamāse ūnakasaññī, aññatra samayā, nahāyati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.57.7.2\">Bu-Pc.57.7.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1115</a>If it is an interval of less than a half-month, and he perceives it "
"as less, and he bathes, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.2.2"
msgid "Ūnakaddhamāse vematiko, aññatra samayā, nahāyati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an interval of less than a half-month, but he is unsure if it is, "
"and he bathes, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.2.3"
msgid ""
"Ūnakaddhamāse atirekasaññī, aññatra samayā, nahāyati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an interval of less than a half-month, but he perceives it as more, "
"and he bathes, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.</p"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc29
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.2.4"
msgid "Atirekaddhamāse ūnakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1116</a>If it is an interval of more than a half-"
"month, but he perceives it as less, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.2.5"
msgid "Atirekaddhamāse vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an interval of more than a half-month, but he is unsure if it is, "
"he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.2.6"
msgid "Atirekaddhamāse atirekasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is an interval of more than a half-month, and he perceives it as more, "
"there is no offense. </p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc30
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.57.7.3\">Bu-Pc.57.7.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1117</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.3.2"
msgid ""
"samaye, addhamāsaṃ nahāyati, atirekaddhamāsaṃ nahāyati, pāraṃ gacchanto "
"nahāyati, sabbapaccantimesu janapadesu, āpadāsu, ummattakassa, "
"ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if there is an appropriate reason; if he bathes at intervals of a half-month;"
" if he bathes at intervals of more than a half-month; if he bathes while "
"crossing a body of water; if he is not in the central Ganges plain; if there "
"are dangers; if he is insane; if he is the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc31
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc57:7.3.3"
msgid "Nahānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1118</a>The seventh rule, the "
"training rule on bathing, is finished.</p>"
